Sentencas: La1-x-ySrxAgyMnO3-delta was synthesized via modified Pechini method.
Titulo: Silver Modified Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Silver (Ag) was incorporated into La1-x-ySrxAgyMnO3-delta cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells as a catalyst precursor for oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Silver Modified Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The La1-x-ySrxAgyMnO3-delta perovskite single phase formed at 800 degrees C, and the solubility of Ag in the crystal lattice of the perovskite was up to 5 mol%.
Titulo: Silver Modified Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The single-phase materials revealed thermal stability in different oxidizing atmospheres up to sintering temperature of the cathode at 1050 degrees C.
Titulo: Silver Modified Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The exsolution of the metallic Ag nanoparticles was performed at 350-600 degrees C in reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Silver Modified Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Scanning electron and scanning transmission electron microcopy revealed a good mechanical contact of the Ag nanoparticles to the surface of the perovskite after reducing conditions.
Titulo: Silver Modified Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical tests of the materials showed a good electrocatalytic effect of nanosized Ag toward oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Silver Modified Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the cathodes revealed the dependence on electrolyte material and exsolution time.
Titulo: Silver Modified Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
